\item Complex number $\myvec{a\\b}$ is expressed as a matrix as 
\begin{align}
\label{Complex}
\myvec{a\\b} = \myvec{a & -b\\ b & a}
\\
\myvec{5\\-3}=\myvec{5&3\\-3&5}
\end{align}
Then,
\begin{align}
\myvec{5\\-3}^3=\myvec{5&3\\-3&5}\myvec{5&3\\-3&5}\myvec{5&3\\-3&5}
\\
\implies \myvec{5\\-3}^3 = \myvec{-10&198\\-198&-10} 
\end{align}
From the equation \ref{Complex}
\begin{align}
\implies \myvec{5\\-3}^3=\myvec{-10\\-198}
\end{align}
